  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Total Knee Arthroplasty tibial insert wear credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for finite-element (FE) contact-mechanics prediction of polyethylene tibial insert wear in a total knee arthroplasty (TKA) implant under standard ISO 14243-1 gait loading. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case wear operating conditions for a Class II TKA device at Model Risk Level 3. Full 13-factor assessment: all 13 factors assessed at MRL 3, all meeting or exceeding required credibility levels. Sensitivity analysis over tibial component alignment (±3° varus/valgus) and contact-area uncertainty is documented.",
